        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 7:56AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 756 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles west of Zella, or 13 miles east of Dilley, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Zella and Fowlerton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
